text: New Hanover County Courthouse New Hanover County Courthouse is a historic courthouse building located in Wilmington, North Carolina and is the seat of New Hanover County.http://www.nccourts.org/Courts/CRS/NCMap/CourthouseDetail.asp?id=75 It was designed by Alfred Eichberg. The courthouse was erected in 1892 at corner of 3rd Street and Princess Street. An annex was built in 1925. == References == Category:Buildings and structures in Wilmington, North Carolina Category:County courthouses in North Carolina Category:Courthouses on the National Register of Historic Places in North Carolina Category:National Register of Historic Places in New Hanover County, North Carolina
